# Vision OS 3.0 — .gitignore
# THIS FILE IS THE BOUNDARY RECORD. Git tracks the markdown wiki + framework. Binaries, secrets,
# machine state, and everything listed under "Confidential" stay local — never committed, anywhere.
#
# The one-boundary model: everything owner-specific lives in Vault/. In the owner's own PRIVATE
# repo, non-sensitive Vault/ markdown IS committed (that is the backup). /export removes Vault/
# wholesale, leaving a clean shareable framework.
#
# Flagging a project confidential = appending its folder under "Confidential" below, in the same
# breath. This file is the ONLY confidentiality record — there is no lock file and no registry.

# ── Confidential — whole-folder, never committed ────────────────────────────
# (confidential folders are appended here by flagging a project confidential)

# ── Obsidian & plugin machine data ──────────────────────────────────────────
.obsidian/
.smart-env/
.makemd/

# ── Claude Code local settings (machine-specific) ───────────────────────────
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/launch.json

# ── Local app sandboxes — disposable working copies, their own git, never backed up ──
Vault/projects/*/*-app-draft/

# ── Binary / large source files — local only, never git ────────────────────
*.pdf
*.PDF
*.xlsx
*.xls
*.xlsm
*.docx
*.doc
*.pptx
*.ppt
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.png
*.gif
*.webp
*.svg
*.ico
*.mp3
*.mp4
*.mov
*.zip
*.7z

# ── Credentials & secrets ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
.env
.env.*
.envrc
credentials
credentials.*
secrets
secrets.*
*recovery*code*
*backup*code*

# ── Python bytecode ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# ── OS / editor noise ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
*.tmp
*.tmp.*
*~
